## Emphasis

You can use *italic text* or **bold text** for emphasis.

You can also use ~~strikethrough~~ text.

## Combinations

Here's a paragraph with **bold text**, *italic text*, `inline code`, and a [link](https://example.com) all together.

## Accessibility

All replaced elements maintain proper semantic HTML:

- Headings use `<h1>`-`<h6>` tags
- Links use `<a>` tags with proper attributes
- Paragraphs use `<p>` tags
- Lists use `<ul>`, `<ol>`, and `<li>` tags
- Tables use proper `<table>`, `<thead>`, `<tbody>`, `<tr>`, `<th>`, and `<td>` tags

The USWDS prose styling ensures all elements meet WCAG 2.1 AA accessibility standards.
